                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d758">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.021/1–2649: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-01-26T18:00:00+08:00"
                            >January 26, 1949—6 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received January 27—3:35 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>229. Note just received from Foreign Office states they will stop receiving
                    communications on February 3 at 5 p. m. Note adds that Foreign Office will stop
                    work February 4 and resume work February 5 at 8 a. m. at No. 68 [–70] Fuhsing
                    Road, Shameen, Canton.</p>
                <p>Sent Department 229; repeated Canton 10.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
